      <h3>Contact</h3>

      <p>Democratic Justice is an investigative publication. If you have information about institutional misconduct, financial irregularities, or governance failures within democratic organizations, we want to hear from you.</p>

      <h3>Send a tip</h3>

      <p><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:proof@democraticjustice.org">proof@democraticjustice.org</a></p>

      <p>If your information involves sensitive material or your identity requires protection, say so in your initial contact and we will discuss secure communication options before you share anything further.</p>

      <h3>What makes a strong tip</h3>

      <p>The strongest tips come with documentation: filings, correspondence, financial records, meeting minutes, recordings, or other verifiable material. We prioritize tips that can be substantiated with primary sources because our reporting is built on provable claims, not allegations.</p>

      <p>That said, you do not need a complete evidentiary package to reach out. If you know something is wrong and can point us in the right direction, that is enough to start a conversation.</p>

      <h3>Source protection</h3>

      <p>We take source protection seriously. We will not reveal a confidential source's identity without their explicit consent. If we cannot adequately protect a source in a given situation, we will say so before they share sensitive information.</p>

      <h3>General inquiries</h3>

      <p>For questions about published reporting, correction requests, or other correspondence, contact us at <a href="mailto:proof@democraticjustice.org">proof@democraticjustice.org</a>.</p>

      <h3>Mailing address</h3>

      <p>Democratic Justice<br>Marion County, West Virginia</p>
